<br>
The person responsible for signing the act that put the words into the Pledge intended for the words to refer to the Almighty, or the Judeo-Christian God.  <br>
<br>
I mean, if the pledge stated &quot;One nation, under Mickey Mouse,&quot; would you argue that the words meant mice in general, or maybe the spirit of Disney?  Mickey Mouse is the name of Mickey Mouse, God is the name of God.<br>
<br>
The most obvious conclusion is that &quot;under God&quot; in the Pledge of Allegiance means God, not a spiritual sense, not a belief system to unite us all, not multiple Gods (I don't see an S there!).<br>
